value.name: Full Circle
value.overview: The series from Neil LaBute aims to examine "the human condition and relationships through a series of conversations between 11 people", whose lives are intertwined, unbeknownst to them. Each episode takes place in a restaurant and is a conversation between two characters. One of the character's storylines then will carry over into the next episode through a conversation with a new character. That character will then be featured in the following episode. The process will continue until the final episode.

value.name: Full Circle
value.overview: Full Circle is a short-lived American soap opera that aired on CBS from June 27, 1960 to March 10, 1961. The half-hour series starred Dyan Cannon and Jean Byron, and was the first American soap opera to be broadcast live from Hollywood.

value.name: Full Circle
value.overview: An investigation into a botched kidnapping uncovers long-held secrets connecting multiple characters and cultures in present day New York City.

value.name: Anderson Cooper Full Circle
value.overview: Anderson Cooper anchors this show that provides the news in a fun and interactive ways as viewers get to engage and have a say in the stories that are covered.

value.name: Full Circle with Michael Palin
value.overview: Michael Palin travels to 18 countries around the rim of the Pacific Ocean.
